The topologic coordinates vary from 1 to MAX.
Choose min and max for each topologic coordinate.

Remark: to define a surface in a structured hexahedron
it is necessary to define an interval reduced to 1 point

Example: S34; I; 34; STRUCTURED_HEXAHEDRON; 
2;5;  4;8;  1;1;
Extract the quadrangles of 3 slices
from 2 to 5 in I-coordinates, 
from 4 to 8 in J-coordinates,
obtained for K=1.

Example: S35; I; 35; STRUCTURED_QUADRANGLE; 
2;5;  4;6;
Extract the quadrangles
from 2 to 5 in I-coordinates, 
from 4 to 6 in J-coordinates.
